Napoli striker Victor Osimhen has hinted he’s ready for his comeback with a protective mask after multiple facial fractures that required six plaques and 18 screws. The forward has been out of action since a horrific clash of heads with Inter defender Milan Skriniar on November 21. The surgeon, who performed the operation to stabilise the fractures described it as a “compression injury. The kinetic force generated by the crushing of Osimhen’s face against the back of Skriniar’s head did devastating damage.”   Osun 2022: Ogunbiyi denies alliance with Adeleke     I can never attack Tinubu – Orji Kalu     FACT-CHECK: Did Ishola, Lam Adesina, Ajimobi, Alao-Akala,…   It took six plaques and 18 screws to stabilise the various fractures in his face. - Advertisement - Osimhen has returned to training this week with the aid of a protective mask and showed it off with a post on social media, along with a hint the time of his comeback is getting close. The 23-year-old pulled out of the Africa Cup of Nations for Nigeria after contracting COVID-19 last month, the second time he has been infected. It’s possible Osimhen will be on the bench for tomorrow’s Serie A game between Napoli and Bologna. (www.football-italia.net)